				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
				content: "Abraham recovered his son from the dead, inasmuch as his life was spared unexpectedly; ‘in a hidden sense’, because the sacrifice of Isaac was a type of our Lord’s Crucifixion."
			},
					3431: {
				id_comment: 3431,
				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
